        <abstract> 
<p>Sends a letter from J. D. Hague confirming his earlier observation [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">8788</hi>] of frightened behaviour of ants when they come upon dead ants. CD had asked for confirmation because J. T. Moggridge had suggested that the ants’ behaviour was alarm at the scent of the observer’s fingers.</p> 
